  <ethicsAndSummary>
    <summary>The aim of the study is to investigate, in an Australian population of pregnant women,
      whether the treatment of periodontal disease during pregnancy prevents pre-term birth and
      other complications of pregnancy. Dental screening and periodontal treatment protocols have
      been based on standard techniques employed by hygienists that can be readily applied to the
      general obstetric population.</summary>
